  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project &quot;Contribution to Improving Tax and Fiscal Governance in the Mugina and Bukinanyana Commune of Cibitoke Province&quot;

CIDEP ( Centre d#appui aux Initiatives locales de D&#xE9;veloppement et d#assistance aux Personnes vuln&#xE9;rables)

The different planning instruments adopted by the Government of Burundi such as the Strategic Framework for Growth and Poverty Reduction (PRSP II), the Prospective Study of Burundi 2025 as well as the Development Objectives (SDGs) reserve an important place for the Decentralization and community development. However, the project is ultimately aimed at strengthening decentralization.
The project conforms to the spirit of the Constitution of the Republic of Burundi in the section on local communities from article 262 to article 267. It is also inspired by the national decentralization policy adopted in 2009 in the country. axis 5 talking about fiscal and financial decentralization.
The project is in line with the municipal law of 2014, particularly in these articles 15, 19, 49 and 51, which paves the way for citizenparticipation in the development of municipalities which are, as stipulated in Articles 1 and 6, pillars of community development.
The project would also help the municipal authorities to implement the content of the law on the reform of the municipal taxation of2016.</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="90">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Centre d#appui aux Initiatives loca D&#xE9;veloppement et d#assistance aux P</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Support Center for Local Initiatives for Development and Assistance to Vulnerable Persons, &quot;CIDEP&quot; in acronym, is a non-profit association of Burundi law approved in 2011 by the Ministerial Ordinance N &#xB0; 530/108 of 3/02 / 2011. The Vision is the construction of a peaceful Burundi where households are actors of sustainable development.
The Mission is to Contribute to the promotion of sustainable development in Burundi. The strategic objectives of CIDEP is to achieve its mission, the organization CIDEP works on four main objectives; Contribute to peacebuilding by promoting social cohesion through inclusive community events and community peace and social cohesion agreements; Promote the financial empowerment of RDExCs youth and women; Promote sexual and reproductive health from acommunity development perspective; Promoting fiscal responsibility and fiscal and budgetary governance at the local and national levels with the aim of contributing to sustainable promotion. The Valuesis the Creativity, Innovation, Collaboration, Transparency.</narrative>
  </participating-org>
